div.span: An idea generation phase can result in submissions with simlar characteristics. In such cases the evaluators face challenges during the assessment.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 262px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

b.font: Lack of shared understanding of selection criteria

font.div: When the selection criteria are strictly defined, the evaluators might assess the ideas in a superficial way and fail to achieve the optimal results.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 259px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: Selecting the best ideas requires a certain level of expertise, especially when the idea assessment requires domain-specific knowledge.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 262px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: The raters have diverse opinions due to different levels of expertise, lack of shared understanding or personal goals.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 259px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

span.b: Too many ideas to be processed

div.span: As human resources are usually very limited, the evaluation team has to come up with a good strategy on how to deal with the workload.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 262px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

span.b: Fear of missing out on good ideas

div.span: In many cases the raters deploy hard criteria to reduce the amount of ideas, which might result in missing out on good ideas.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 239px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

span.span: The idea assessment often can be influenced by personal relationships between the raters and ideators, certain interest on the domain or other subjective factors.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 262px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: Even when the submission requirements are set clear, ideators submit ideas that do not fully meet the expectations.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 259px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: In several cases taking into consideration the opinion of the crowd can be a good solution. Unfortunately, the opinion of the crowd can often be biased or misleading.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 262px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.div: In some cases, the croteria can increase the complexity of the evaluation when they 1) are not strictly define, 2) are too many, 3) are too fine-graned or 4) are too coarse-grained.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 129px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.div: Affinity Diagrams are useful for sorting large amounts of ideas into groups. The technique facilitates complexity reduction.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 155px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.div: The four categories method categorizes the pile of ideas by their perceived abstractness. In this way the teams can take into consideration also ideas with low degree of rationality but potentially interesting.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 149px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.div: Similar to the Four Categories method, the Bingo Selection lets its users categorize ideas into various factors like business applications.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 169px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

span.font: The Now-Wow-How matrix supports the idea selection process by targeting two criteria namely the degree of idea originality and the difficulty of idea implementation. The resulting ideas (Wow ideas) would be those that require both relatively low implementation effort and high degree of novelty.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 147px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.font: Post-it voting facilitates the selection of the best ideas, through multiple voting. The method ensures more proportional representation and allows for multiple ideas to be further pursued.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 289px; max-width: 129px; width: 129px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

span.font: The goal of an innovation contest is to identify the winning ideas among a pile of many submissions. Online innovation contests can result in hundreds and thousands of submissions. The determination of the best ideas is a challenging process that goes through different phases.

span.font: Innovation Funnel: The innovation funnel features commonly the four phases included in an innovation contest namely, the generation phase, the filtering phase, the shortlisting phase, and the winner determination phase.
